FINE * Contents condition: Ex-Library with usual neat stamps and labels. Clean, crisp & tight. No annotations or marks to text, no tanning. Very slight colouration to page edges. VG+* Illustrations: None.* Pages: 191 pp. text.* Product Description:- Hundreds of years in the future, Earthmen have moved out into the galaxy of inhabited worlds, but only through the gift of advanced technology from alien interstellar traders. Earthmen do not dominate among inhabited worlds, as many races are older and wiser - in fact, space travellers from Earth are second-class citizens or worse on most of the planets they visit.* This is a NEAR FINE ex-library copy of the 1st./1st. with minor faults reducing it to VG+.* 2003-06-16. n.

Author's first novel and a Nebula Award nominee. "She was Cian. He was Human. They were lovers". 166 pages. Irregular 2" x 3/4" area effaced [and about a third of that torn off completely] along the bottom edge of the rear cover, else would be a VG+ copy [cheap paper tanning] with store stamp inside the front cover. .

Octavo, cloth. First edition. "An intricate and melancholy tale of love and biological mystery on a distant world." - Robert Silverberg. The author's first novel. 1978 Nebula nominee. Anatomy of Wonder (2004) II-356. A review copy with review slip, publisher's promotional sheet and publicity photograph of Dozois laid in. A fine copy in fine dust jacket. (#157632).
